00:00:20,167 --> 00:00:21,716
Hey, Day!

5
00:00:22,488 --> 00:00:23,646
What brings you here?

6
00:00:24,488 --> 00:00:26,231
Night told me you’re studying abroad.

7
00:00:26,231 --> 00:00:27,727
Why didn’t you tell me you’re back?

8
00:00:28,037 --> 00:00:28,642
I’m blind.

9
00:00:29,602 --> 00:00:32,447
Have you seen his face before?

10
00:00:32,447 --> 00:00:34,778
With these eyes, how can I see him?

11
00:00:34,778 --> 00:00:37,115
Not only is his voice handsome,

12
00:00:38,155 --> 00:00:39,022
but so is his face.

13
00:00:39,022 --> 00:00:39,704
Wait.

14
00:00:40,193 --> 00:00:41,206
You played men's doubles?

15
00:00:43,234 --> 00:00:44,841
What about the fact that you cheated on me?

16
00:00:44,841 --> 00:00:45,787
Is it all me, too?

17
00:00:46,651 --> 00:00:48,651
Keng, you son of a bitch.

18
00:00:49,405 --> 00:00:50,068
Get lost!

19
00:00:50,068 --> 00:00:50,926
What the f*ck are you doing?

20
00:00:51,335 --> 00:00:53,110
You can stay here in the meantime.

21
00:00:53,110 --> 00:00:54,384
I'm two months pregnant.

22
00:00:56,721 --> 00:00:57,506
who's that?

23
00:00:57,506 --> 00:00:58,721
Introduce him to us.

24
00:00:58,721 --> 00:00:59,954
He's my caretaker.

25
00:01:00,486 --> 00:01:01,192
His name is Mhok.

26
00:01:01,192 --> 00:01:04,233
Gee told us that your caretaker was hot.

27
00:01:04,233 --> 00:01:05,195
He really is.

28
00:01:08,786 --> 00:01:10,003
Can I crash here tonight?

29
00:01:10,786 --> 00:01:11,823
Why?

30
00:01:12,304 --> 00:01:14,473
Well, you're dead drunk.

31
00:01:14,866 --> 00:01:16,612
I'll stay and help out in case something happens.

32
00:01:51,839 --> 00:01:53,219
Wake up! It’s raining.

33
00:01:53,219 --> 00:01:54,126
It’s pouring.

34
00:01:54,708 --> 00:01:55,919
What the–

35
00:01:56,526 --> 00:01:58,526
Gosh, I got water in my mouth.

36
00:02:03,001 --> 00:02:06,000
Phi, you’ve just proved I was right when I called you an asshole.

37
00:02:06,996 --> 00:02:08,742
Wait, wait, wait.

38
00:02:09,546 --> 00:02:11,349
What did you just call me?

39
00:02:14,732 --> 00:02:15,834
What, Mister?

40
00:02:18,000 --> 00:02:19,602
That’s not what I just heard.

41
00:02:20,230 --> 00:02:21,368
What was it?

42
00:02:21,762 --> 00:02:22,849
Call me that again.

43
00:02:23,469 --> 00:02:24,336
No.

44
00:02:25,338 --> 00:02:26,775
I don’t want any more big brother.

45
00:02:28,862 --> 00:02:29,635
Yeah?

46
00:02:30,565 --> 00:02:31,595
What do you want me to be then?

47
00:02:33,924 --> 00:02:34,734
Well.

48
00:02:35,664 --> 00:02:36,600
A caretaker.

49
00:02:38,313 --> 00:02:38,934
Why?

50
00:02:40,313 --> 00:02:41,213
Just go.

51
00:02:42,001 --> 00:02:43,160
I'm going to take a shower.

52
00:02:43,160 --> 00:02:43,888
Leave.

53
00:02:45,251 --> 00:02:46,800
I said leave.

54
00:02:47,287 --> 00:02:48,227
I'm not leaving.

55
00:02:49,287 --> 00:02:52,037
I'll go after you call me that again.

56
00:02:52,429 --> 00:02:53,199
Phi.

57
00:02:55,847 --> 00:02:56,739
Or what?

58
00:02:59,296 --> 00:03:00,326
Listen to you.

59
00:03:00,580 --> 00:03:02,113
You actually want me to stay, huh?

60
00:03:03,871 --> 00:03:04,871
Hey.

61
00:03:07,491 --> 00:03:09,280
It's up to you.

62
00:03:09,637 --> 00:03:10,863
I can be here all day.

63
00:03:15,427 --> 00:03:16,201
Fine.

64
00:03:17,218 --> 00:03:18,239
Whatever you say, Phi.

65
00:03:19,338 --> 00:03:20,063
Phi Mhok.

66
00:03:22,246 --> 00:03:23,190
Are you happy now?

67
00:03:24,852 --> 00:03:26,021
I didn't quite hear that.

68
00:03:26,840 --> 00:03:27,878
Can you say it again?

69
00:03:28,132 --> 00:03:28,897
Just go.

70
00:03:28,897 --> 00:03:30,414
I already did what you asked.

71
00:03:30,555 --> 00:03:31,879
Go.

72
00:03:33,312 --> 00:03:34,805
That's all you needed to do,

73
00:03:34,944 --> 00:03:36,015
Nong Day.

74
00:03:37,677 --> 00:03:39,169
Leave.

75
00:03:40,420 --> 00:03:41,586
Can I borrow a shirt?

76
00:03:43,445 --> 00:03:44,279
Okay?

77
00:03:44,802 --> 00:03:46,187
Just take the one you want.

78
00:03:48,948 --> 00:03:49,957
Out of bed.

79
00:03:50,126 --> 00:03:50,953
Fine.

80
00:04:06,000 --> 00:04:07,775
Day, I'm making you soup.

81
00:04:07,992 --> 00:04:09,348
I'll make you the bread once I'm done.

82
00:04:09,714 --> 00:04:10,583
That's okay.

83
00:04:10,583 --> 00:04:11,492
I'll do it myself.

84
00:04:11,633 --> 00:04:12,328
Hm?

85
00:04:13,020 --> 00:04:14,034
I'll spread the jam myself.

86
00:04:14,034 --> 00:04:14,782
Really?

87
00:04:16,875 --> 00:04:18,312
Well then, let me see.

88
00:04:18,312 --> 00:04:20,895
Let’s see if the chef's son got skills.

89
00:04:22,063 --> 00:04:23,335
Let me show you.

90
00:04:28,772 --> 00:04:29,500
Phi.

91
00:04:30,459 --> 00:04:31,548
Do you want the jam?

92
00:04:31,548 --> 00:04:32,374
Yes, I do.

93
00:04:38,813 --> 00:04:40,362
How about this?

94
00:04:40,620 --> 00:04:41,614
Good.

95
00:04:41,614 --> 00:04:43,014
But go a little to the left.

96
00:04:43,155 --> 00:04:44,038
Okay.

97
00:04:46,662 --> 00:04:48,000
You will also get the taste of my hand.

98
00:04:51,991 --> 00:04:52,843
Done.

99
00:04:54,759 --> 00:04:55,597
Let's see.

100
00:04:55,872 --> 00:04:57,309
Hey, that's quite good.

101
00:04:57,866 --> 00:04:59,191
You've got skills.

102
00:04:59,360 --> 00:05:00,542
Of course.

103
00:05:14,762 --> 00:05:15,606
Hey.

104
00:05:16,050 --> 00:05:18,050
I turned it off last night.

105
00:05:23,898 --> 00:05:24,587
Oops.

106
00:05:24,925 --> 00:05:26,884
Phi, is my phone malfunctioning?

107
00:05:27,418 --> 00:05:28,567
Notifications keep popping up.

108
00:05:28,567 --> 00:05:29,418
Can you check?

109
00:05:29,418 --> 00:05:30,736
Here, let me check it for you.

110
00:05:34,119 --> 00:05:35,048
It's not malfunctioning.

111
00:05:35,330 --> 00:05:38,542
People from last night posted photos and tagged you.

112
00:05:39,022 --> 00:05:39,615
Really?

113
00:05:39,615 --> 00:05:40,571
Yes, photos from the party.

114
00:05:41,599 --> 00:05:42,754
Let me read the caption for you.

115
00:05:43,957 --> 00:05:46,661
‘Holy shit! Day’s made a comeback.’

116
00:05:50,267 --> 00:05:52,633
‘You’re wicked as always, Day.’

117
00:05:58,127 --> 00:06:00,972
‘I’m jelly! I want to be taken care of by Phi Mhok too.’

118
00:06:01,448 --> 00:06:02,885
Oh, please.

119
00:06:03,153 --> 00:06:05,604
You must have added that latter one yourself.

120
00:06:05,604 --> 00:06:06,696
It's true.

121
00:06:06,696 --> 00:06:08,696
If you don't believe me, you can read it using an app.

122
00:06:08,696 --> 00:06:09,824
You making it up?

123
00:06:13,179 --> 00:06:16,109
(‘I’m jelly! I want to be taken care of by Phi Mhok too.’)

124
00:06:17,398 --> 00:06:18,196
Fine.

125
00:06:19,398 --> 00:06:20,741
You didn't add it.

126
00:06:20,901 --> 00:06:21,838
Right.

127
00:06:22,542 --> 00:06:24,394
You should post something too.

128
00:06:24,394 --> 00:06:25,698
Your friends had missed you.

129
00:06:27,109 --> 00:06:28,743
What should I post all of a sudden?

130
00:06:29,350 --> 00:06:31,660
Photos of anything.

131
00:06:31,866 --> 00:06:32,914
Really?

132
00:06:33,703 --> 00:06:36,514
This can work. Your bread.

133
00:06:36,514 --> 00:06:37,726
Your breakfast.

134
00:06:37,899 --> 00:06:38,561
This one?

135
00:06:38,561 --> 00:06:39,330
Let me help.

136
00:06:40,372 --> 00:06:41,674
Hold it here.

137
00:06:42,378 --> 00:06:43,529
Turn on the camera.

138
00:06:46,261 --> 00:06:47,335
You'll be the one taking.

139
00:06:48,128 --> 00:06:49,114
Go ahead.

140
00:06:49,114 --> 00:06:49,781
The frame is good?

141
00:06:49,781 --> 00:06:50,982
Yes. Tap the shutter button.

142
00:06:50,982 --> 00:06:51,978
One, two, three.

143
00:06:53,689 --> 00:06:54,476
Let me see.

144
00:06:54,730 --> 00:06:55,492
Is it good?

145
00:06:55,676 --> 00:06:56,698
It's nice.

146
00:06:57,676 --> 00:06:58,654
The caption…

147
00:06:59,121 --> 00:06:59,716
Caption?

148
00:06:59,716 --> 00:07:00,924
My bread-fast.

149
00:07:01,422 --> 00:07:02,225
Hold on.

150
00:07:04,366 --> 00:07:06,000
My bread-fast.

151
00:07:06,535 --> 00:07:07,260
Post it.

152
00:07:10,021 --> 00:07:11,031
I just did.

153
00:07:11,031 --> 00:07:11,739
Let me see.

154
00:07:13,593 --> 00:07:14,832
Yes. Good job.

155
00:07:20,911 --> 00:07:22,911
(‘Day, who’s the other guy?’)

156
00:07:24,283 --> 00:07:25,220
Come on.

157
00:07:25,473 --> 00:07:26,395
The fun is ruined.

158
00:07:34,663 --> 00:07:37,001
(‘Day, aren't you coming to cheer for your friend?’)

159
00:07:37,649 --> 00:07:38,341
Wait!

160
00:07:39,548 --> 00:07:41,238
Gee has a game today.

161
00:07:41,845 --> 00:07:43,704
Can you check? Is it right?

162
00:07:46,959 --> 00:07:50,424
I think so. She checked in at a badminton court five minutes ago.

163
00:07:52,595 --> 00:07:54,048
If this was a normal situation,

164
00:07:54,302 --> 00:07:55,835
I'd be right on the bleachers for her.

165
00:07:56,511 --> 00:07:58,511
We can make it a normal situation.

166
00:07:58,833 --> 00:08:00,213
Do you want to go, Nong Day?

167
00:08:00,679 --> 00:08:02,144
Phi Mhok here is going to take care of you.

168
00:08:05,123 --> 00:08:06,982
Let's eat first.

169
00:08:07,678 --> 00:08:09,227
Here’s your soup.

170
00:08:09,227 --> 00:08:10,688
You eat the bread I made first.

171
00:08:10,688 --> 00:08:11,188
Sure.

172
00:08:11,188 --> 00:08:13,051
You eat the soup I made.

173
00:08:49,244 --> 00:08:51,244
Directed by Noppharnach Chaiyahwimhon

174
00:08:52,247 --> 00:08:53,314
Oh, wow.

175
00:08:53,455 --> 00:08:55,402
It's like I’m reading to my own kid or something.

176
00:08:56,953 --> 00:08:57,826
Just do it.

177
00:08:58,220 --> 00:08:59,347
Come on. Read.

178
00:08:59,347 --> 00:09:00,505
I'm listening.

179
00:09:01,097 --> 00:09:01,767
Quickly.

180
00:09:05,370 --> 00:09:09,483
Last Twilight: Until The Last Light Goes Out.

181
00:09:13,947 --> 00:09:18,000
Once upon a time, there was a kid named Mee.

182
00:09:18,762 --> 00:09:20,762
Mee was an ordinary child just like the others.

183
00:09:21,307 --> 00:09:27,955
Until one day, a wicked wizard put a curse on her, causing her body to gradually fade away.

184
00:09:32,420 --> 00:09:33,716
Mee was really sad.

185
00:09:33,956 --> 00:09:36,632
She only stayed inside her room and refused to meet anyone.

186
00:09:37,272 --> 00:09:40,314
However, one day, Mee couldn't stand her loneliness any longer.

187
00:09:41,036 --> 00:09:43,290
She decided to step outside her house.

188
00:09:50,516 --> 00:09:52,065
Day, we're at the court.

189
00:09:56,391 --> 00:09:58,137
Should we go on the bleachers?

190
00:09:59,658 --> 00:10:00,490
Let's go.

191
00:10:03,408 --> 00:10:04,704
Hello, Coach.

192
00:10:04,704 --> 00:10:05,408
Hi, Mhok.

193
00:10:05,726 --> 00:10:07,557
- Hello, Coach.
- It's Coach Aek.

194
00:10:07,557 --> 00:10:09,514
I'm glad you're here.

195
00:10:09,772 --> 00:10:10,507
Let's root for Gee.

196
00:10:10,507 --> 00:10:11,603
- Sure.
- Of course.

197
00:10:13,336 --> 00:10:17,590
Mee went to the playground where she used to play with her friends.

198
00:10:18,818 --> 00:10:22,846
However, no one could see Mee that day.

199
00:10:56,397 --> 00:10:58,397
Whoo-hoo!

200
00:10:59,375 --> 00:11:01,150
Gee has just walked in.

201
00:11:02,940 --> 00:11:04,208
How does she look?

202
00:11:06,166 --> 00:11:07,743
I think she looks very confident.

203
00:11:10,289 --> 00:11:12,204
She's trying to play it cool.

204
00:11:12,954 --> 00:11:14,447
It's a sport psychology.

205
00:11:14,687 --> 00:11:15,643
To intimidate the opponent.

206
00:11:17,502 --> 00:11:18,461
You know what?

207
00:11:18,926 --> 00:11:22,504
When we were unknown players, we didn't have anyone cheering for us.

208
00:11:22,504 --> 00:11:23,898
We were each other's support.

209
00:11:24,935 --> 00:11:28,794
When we lost, we cried together with arms around each other's shoulders.

210
00:11:30,355 --> 00:11:32,468
Oh, how I miss it.

211
00:11:36,476 --> 00:11:38,476
I won't get to see those pictures again.

212
00:11:45,476 --> 00:11:50,828
Hey, since we're here, I'll be your sports commentator.

213
00:11:51,476 --> 00:11:52,184
Okay?

214
00:11:52,635 --> 00:11:53,391
Mhm.

215
00:11:58,043 --> 00:12:00,043
They're in the court now.

216
00:12:02,178 --> 00:12:06,882
Gee is wearing a blue shirt, blue shorts, and light blue sports shoes.

217
00:12:07,133 --> 00:12:09,133
Her badminton racket is…

218
00:12:10,128 --> 00:12:11,255
bright green.

219
00:12:12,610 --> 00:12:16,188
Why don't you just tell me her lips and eye colors too since you’re so specific?

220
00:12:21,006 --> 00:12:22,274
A rally begins.

221
00:12:22,274 --> 00:12:28,433
- Gee hits it.
- She hits it.

222
00:12:29,838 --> 00:12:32,880
Yeah!

223
00:12:32,880 --> 00:12:33,544
Oh.

224
00:12:33,817 --> 00:12:34,597
It was a drop shot.

225
00:12:35,555 --> 00:12:36,578
Gee earns the point.

226
00:12:37,448 --> 00:12:39,279
Now that was too little information.

227
00:12:39,519 --> 00:12:42,505
They hit and hit and hit.

228
00:12:43,011 --> 00:12:44,149
What's the fun in that?

229
00:12:45,360 --> 00:12:46,222
Well.

230
00:12:47,538 --> 00:12:48,918
I don't know how to play badminton.

231
00:12:49,319 --> 00:12:50,615
I have no idea how to comment.

232
00:12:53,222 --> 00:12:55,673
Gee prefers backcourt games.

233
00:12:56,303 --> 00:12:59,599
She moves her opponent to the left and right.

234
00:13:05,636 --> 00:13:08,819
Once her opponent is tired, she will do her drop shot.

235
00:13:11,234 --> 00:13:13,234
Yeah!

236
00:13:21,580 --> 00:13:23,157
Wow, as if you can see.

237
00:13:24,225 --> 00:13:25,662
I'll just listen to you instead.

238
00:13:42,276 --> 00:13:43,994
I think her opponent can read her strategy.

239
00:13:44,328 --> 00:13:45,652
The game is tighter now.

240
00:13:47,620 --> 00:13:49,958
Gee isn't built for long games.

241
00:13:50,227 --> 00:13:52,452
She becomes slower towards the end.

242
00:14:18,378 --> 00:14:19,279
The deciding point.

243
00:15:09,216 --> 00:15:10,535
Gee did it.

244
00:15:11,216 --> 00:15:12,348
She won.

245
00:15:24,998 --> 00:15:28,322
For Mee, even though no one saw her,

246
00:15:28,833 --> 00:15:35,509
seeing everyone’s smiles and laughter was worth stepping out of her house.

247
00:15:44,113 --> 00:15:45,158
You did so great.

248
00:15:45,355 --> 00:15:47,662
I was almost knocked off my game.

249
00:15:47,662 --> 00:15:49,121
Even so, you are great.

250
00:15:49,121 --> 00:15:51,802
- Thank you so much.
- You don't have to tell me. She's smiling so widely her eyes become smaller.

251
00:15:51,802 --> 00:15:53,540
Bye.

252
00:15:53,832 --> 00:15:54,719
Gee is right in front of you.

253
00:15:56,804 --> 00:15:57,776
Ahem.

254
00:16:00,959 --> 00:16:01,973
Day!

255
00:16:03,832 --> 00:16:04,619
Ow!

256
00:16:04,987 --> 00:16:05,987
Gee.

257
00:16:05,987 --> 00:16:07,241
You're all sweaty.

258
00:16:07,241 --> 00:16:08,744
What? You can't stand a little sweat?

259
00:16:10,306 --> 00:16:11,530
Gee.

260
00:16:13,896 --> 00:16:15,066
Congrats.

261
00:16:16,023 --> 00:16:17,600
Thanks a lot for coming.

262
00:16:18,422 --> 00:16:19,690
I thought you wouldn't come.

263
00:16:20,944 --> 00:16:22,070
Thank Phi Mhok.

264
00:16:22,633 --> 00:16:24,000
He urged me to come.

265
00:16:25,174 --> 00:16:26,119
You're awesome.

266
00:16:26,964 --> 00:16:27,878
Thank you.

267
00:16:28,895 --> 00:16:29,882
What did you just call him?

268
00:16:30,782 --> 00:16:31,541
Phi.

269
00:16:31,766 --> 00:16:32,490
Why?

270
00:16:33,448 --> 00:16:35,138
Last night, the pronoun was still polite and distant.

271
00:16:36,618 --> 00:16:37,646
What's up?

272
00:16:38,266 --> 00:16:41,097
Should we Blame the Stars for this?

273
00:16:42,927 --> 00:16:43,955
Damn you.

274
00:16:44,265 --> 00:16:46,054
Blame the Stars, my ass.

275
00:16:46,393 --> 00:16:47,523
Blame you.

276
00:16:47,523 --> 00:16:48,337
What?

277
00:16:48,337 --> 00:16:50,084
You're suddenly blushing.

278
00:16:50,818 --> 00:16:52,001
I won't come to your next match.

279
00:16:52,776 --> 00:16:55,452
No, I'm kidding.

280
00:16:55,452 --> 00:16:56,483
I'll bring him.

281
00:16:56,833 --> 00:16:58,002
You're awesome.

282
00:16:58,833 --> 00:17:00,000
Since you're here,

283
00:17:00,000 --> 00:17:01,594
