570
00:38:50,920 --> 00:38:53,246
What do you want to eat?

571
00:38:53,746 --> 00:38:54,693
I'll read you the menu.

572
00:38:57,130 --> 00:38:57,961
Enough already.

573
00:38:57,961 --> 00:38:58,698
You're giving me goosebumps.

574
00:38:59,321 --> 00:39:00,779
Order whatever you want.

575
00:39:01,223 --> 00:39:02,393
I'll not complain anymore.

576
00:39:03,033 --> 00:39:04,041
Baby.

577
00:39:04,214 --> 00:39:05,525
Stop it.

578
00:39:06,123 --> 00:39:07,704
Did I do something that upset you?

579
00:39:08,069 --> 00:39:09,048
Drop it.

580
00:39:11,718 --> 00:39:14,807
Let's start from the first dish, spaghetti.

581
00:39:17,662 --> 00:39:18,973
Spaghetti?

582
00:39:32,549 --> 00:39:33,409
It's good.

583
00:39:35,009 --> 00:39:35,878
Day.

584
00:39:36,458 --> 00:39:38,458
You don't have to be so tense when you eat.

585
00:39:40,879 --> 00:39:41,690
Baby.

586
00:39:42,773 --> 00:39:44,454
No matter how messily you eat, you're still cute.

587
00:39:44,454 --> 00:39:45,431
Just eat.

588
00:39:47,868 --> 00:39:50,360
Please don't be in a relationship.

589
00:39:50,716 --> 00:39:51,710
I feel bad for your lover.

590
00:39:53,827 --> 00:39:55,178
The next dish is…

591
00:39:56,979 --> 00:39:57,814
Steak.

592
00:39:58,233 --> 00:39:59,398
That's your knife.

593
00:39:59,954 --> 00:40:01,634
Let's put the spoon here for now.

594
00:40:02,893 --> 00:40:03,958
Now try that, Day.

595
00:40:16,638 --> 00:40:17,586
Are you okay?

596
00:40:19,728 --> 00:40:23,242
When it comes with side dishes, it's hard to eat.

597
00:40:23,994 --> 00:40:26,708
I just don't remember where everything is.

598
00:40:27,872 --> 00:40:28,919
They are all over the plate.

599
00:40:29,756 --> 00:40:30,463
Day.

600
00:40:32,469 --> 00:40:34,881
Try to imagine your plate as a clock face.

601
00:40:37,369 --> 00:40:38,034
Okay.

602
00:40:38,034 --> 00:40:39,705
The steak is at the center.

603
00:40:41,504 --> 00:40:42,696
Your salad is at 10 o’clock.

604
00:40:44,761 --> 00:40:46,321
Your mashed potato is at 2 p.m.

605
00:40:47,687 --> 00:40:48,366
Hey.

606
00:40:49,687 --> 00:40:51,201
Where did you learn this trick?

607
00:40:53,170 --> 00:40:55,367
My preparation is far more than just putting on perfume.

608
00:40:57,554 --> 00:40:58,588
Now you're bragging.

609
00:40:59,321 --> 00:41:00,164
Try it.

610
00:41:02,171 --> 00:41:02,938
Fine.

611
00:41:02,938 --> 00:41:03,851
Am I cutting the meat?

612
00:41:04,769 --> 00:41:07,729
Hold your fork like this. You’re on a date.

613
00:41:08,041 --> 00:41:08,809
Right.

614
00:41:09,449 --> 00:41:10,681
How would I know that?

615
00:41:17,706 --> 00:41:18,894
What is it?

616
00:41:19,487 --> 00:41:20,750
It's too long.

617
00:41:25,576 --> 00:41:27,052
And the last one.

618
00:41:28,184 --> 00:41:28,974
A cake.

619
00:41:30,001 --> 00:41:30,916
A cake?

620
00:41:31,047 --> 00:41:31,791
Right.

621
00:41:32,062 --> 00:41:32,752
Whoa.

622
00:41:32,752 --> 00:41:33,513
Give it a try.

623
00:41:33,814 --> 00:41:39,321
I think if you could eat steak, which is hard, you can eat cake just fine.

624
00:41:40,238 --> 00:41:41,475
Just fine, huh?

625
00:41:41,949 --> 00:41:43,924
This is the hard one.

626
00:41:45,204 --> 00:41:45,880
Why?

627
00:41:48,282 --> 00:41:50,681
The eating part isn't that hard.

628
00:42:03,023 --> 00:42:03,896
Let me guess.

629
00:42:04,585 --> 00:42:07,721
You are looking at the cream on my mouth.

630
00:42:09,590 --> 00:42:12,156
I just don't want to look bad in front of people.

631
00:42:13,363 --> 00:42:15,068
This is not bad, Day.

632
00:42:15,449 --> 00:42:19,281
To be honest, I think you're so damn cute right now.

633
00:42:24,445 --> 00:42:25,608
Cute how?

634
00:42:26,593 --> 00:42:27,775
You should eat too.

635
00:42:27,923 --> 00:42:28,571
Here.

636
00:42:29,166 --> 00:42:30,266
I'll feed you.

637
00:42:36,469 --> 00:42:37,615
You're just pretending to struggle.

638
00:42:38,391 --> 00:42:40,194
I know you want me to feed you.

639
00:42:41,528 --> 00:42:43,241
You're all pretending.

640
00:42:43,568 --> 00:42:45,273
Here you go. Open your mouth.

641
00:42:45,846 --> 00:42:47,181
You open your mouth.

642
00:42:47,181 --> 00:42:48,700
Give it. I'll feed you.

643
00:42:51,734 --> 00:42:53,611
Day. We just dropped it everywhere.

644
00:42:53,611 --> 00:42:55,515
And my mouth is a mess now.

645
00:42:56,463 --> 00:42:59,423
In that split second, Mee didn’t realize

646
00:42:59,980 --> 00:43:02,521
that stepping outside of her dark room into the sunlight

647
00:43:03,116 --> 00:43:07,553
could gradually make her fading body become tangible again.

648
00:43:13,449 --> 00:43:14,957
It's even messier now.

649
00:43:17,565 --> 00:43:18,158
Hey.

650
00:43:18,749 --> 00:43:20,156
You can leave me here.

651
00:43:20,761 --> 00:43:23,106
I'll ask August to take me home.

652
00:43:53,443 --> 00:43:54,214
We’ve arrived.

653
00:43:57,010 --> 00:43:58,612
Night is pretty generous.

654
00:43:58,612 --> 00:44:00,014
He let us take his car.

655
00:44:00,153 --> 00:44:01,532
He didn't even ask where we were going.

656
00:44:03,213 --> 00:44:05,803
Actually, Mom bought me this car.

657
00:44:06,615 --> 00:44:07,870
Hmm.

658
00:44:08,377 --> 00:44:10,160
He takes very good care of your car though.

659
00:44:13,146 --> 00:44:14,929
You've been fooled by him too?

660
00:44:19,418 --> 00:44:20,433
Let's go.

661
00:44:22,079 --> 00:44:23,064
Hey, let me help.

662
00:44:23,064 --> 00:44:24,797
Hold on. I'm coming to your side.

663
00:44:29,984 --> 00:44:30,810
Get up.

664
00:44:43,483 --> 00:44:44,831
Day, we are entering the place.

665
00:44:46,295 --> 00:44:47,161
Yes.

666
00:44:47,969 --> 00:44:48,792
The door.

667
00:44:58,394 --> 00:44:59,281
Let's take the couch.

668
00:45:06,860 --> 00:45:08,439
See? He hasn't come yet.

669
00:45:08,439 --> 00:45:09,610
I told you we didn't have to hurry.

670
00:45:10,646 --> 00:45:11,390
Hey.

671
00:45:11,980 --> 00:45:13,236
You can leave me here.

672
00:45:13,892 --> 00:45:16,389
I'll ask August to take me home.

673
00:45:23,319 --> 00:45:25,319
Yeah, sure.

674
00:45:25,740 --> 00:45:27,021
Will you be okay on your own?

675
00:45:27,487 --> 00:45:28,206
Mhm.

676
00:45:31,374 --> 00:45:32,342
Okay.

677
00:45:46,539 --> 00:45:47,980
Here's your water, sir.

678
00:45:48,725 --> 00:45:49,724
Thank you.

679
00:47:42,982 --> 00:47:44,060
August?

680
00:47:45,939 --> 00:47:46,861
It's me.

681
00:47:59,265 --> 00:48:00,326
He hasn't come yet?

682
00:48:04,923 --> 00:48:07,664
I called but he didn't pick up.

683
00:48:08,664 --> 00:48:10,664
He's probably stuck in the traffic.

684
00:48:13,402 --> 00:48:14,657
It’s just how it is.

685
00:48:15,530 --> 00:48:18,120
He's always late when we meet up.

686
00:48:48,391 --> 00:48:49,169
Come on.

687
00:48:49,542 --> 00:48:50,391
Come with me.

688
00:48:52,324 --> 00:48:53,255
To where?

689
00:48:53,752 --> 00:48:54,821
Just come.

690
00:48:55,504 --> 00:48:56,263
Let's go.

691
00:49:12,201 --> 00:49:13,176
Mind the door.

692
00:49:26,594 --> 00:49:28,159
Nice weather.

693
00:49:28,159 --> 00:49:29,094
Yes.

694
00:49:29,094 --> 00:49:30,641
Want to know where we are?

695
00:49:31,265 --> 00:49:32,296
I do.

696
00:49:32,513 --> 00:49:34,973
Then you must see it for yourself.

697
00:49:35,653 --> 00:49:37,001
Hey, wait.

698
00:49:37,784 --> 00:49:39,380
- Come on, Day.
- Don't leave me.

699
00:49:39,380 --> 00:49:41,156
I'm right here. Just keep walking.

700
00:49:41,156 --> 00:49:42,491
Quickly.

701
00:49:42,786 --> 00:49:44,134
Chop-chop.

702
00:49:44,821 --> 00:49:45,939
Come on.

703
00:49:47,007 --> 00:49:47,954
Are we there yet?

704
00:49:47,954 --> 00:49:48,696
What?

705
00:49:48,696 --> 00:49:49,539
Are we there yet?

706
00:49:49,539 --> 00:49:50,421
A bit further.

707
00:49:50,671 --> 00:49:52,174
Where does this lead?

708
00:49:54,298 --> 00:49:55,863
It leads to me right here.

709
00:50:01,293 --> 00:50:03,293
We're on the Memorial Bridge.

710
00:50:04,126 --> 00:50:05,008
Ah.

711
00:50:05,852 --> 00:50:11,942
When I was working as a technician, I came here a lot at night.

712
00:50:11,942 --> 00:50:13,290
In front of you, there's another bridge.

713
00:50:13,503 --> 00:50:16,342
It’s the green bridge where people like to come and take photos.

714
00:50:17,915 --> 00:50:19,201
You can see the Wat Arun from here.

715
00:50:21,498 --> 00:50:23,205
It’s so beautiful.

716
00:50:24,106 --> 00:50:26,200
It's in the evening and the lights are on.

717
00:50:44,709 --> 00:50:45,501
So.

718
00:50:45,781 --> 00:50:46,989
You're smiling now, huh?

719
00:50:47,899 --> 00:50:49,899
Stop teasing me, Phi Mhok.

720
00:51:39,226 --> 00:51:41,692
Day, we’re at Pak Khlong Talat Flower Market now.

721
00:51:46,480 --> 00:51:50,841
It’d be great if you could choose perfumes as well as places to visit.

722
00:51:55,722 --> 00:51:59,555
Usually, when my lovers were upset with me, I would take them here.

723
00:52:00,467 --> 00:52:04,082
When they saw a bunch of flowers, they all felt better.

724
00:52:06,655 --> 00:52:08,127
Why are you telling me this?

725
00:52:10,729 --> 00:52:12,046
Are you feeling better?

726
00:52:20,902 --> 00:52:23,399
(Mee walked past a colorful flower field.)

727
00:52:23,826 --> 00:52:27,348
(A bright-colored flower was the one to greet her.)

728
00:52:27,442 --> 00:52:31,803
(It's when Mee realized that the curse was gone.)

729
00:53:00,409 --> 00:53:01,220
Ah.

730
00:53:01,810 --> 00:53:02,999
I know this flower.

731
00:53:04,316 --> 00:53:05,402
Hydrangeas.

732
00:53:06,316 --> 00:53:07,354
Rung loved it.

733
00:53:07,354 --> 00:53:08,339
Hold on.

734
00:53:08,559 --> 00:53:11,926
If I'm not mistaken, this flower represents

735
00:53:12,704 --> 00:53:14,083
a heartless person.

736
00:53:17,276 --> 00:53:18,344
It's pretty accurate.

737
00:53:21,051 --> 00:53:22,771
It has one more meaning.

738
00:53:23,661 --> 00:53:25,102
It’s used to say thanks.

739
00:53:26,442 --> 00:53:27,550
Like,

740
00:53:28,761 --> 00:53:33,753
thanks for understanding and accepting my decisions.

741
00:53:40,168 --> 00:53:43,410
Do you know what flower that I like?

742
00:53:47,723 --> 00:53:49,071
Ah…

743
00:53:51,249 --> 00:53:52,272
Roses?

744
00:53:52,955 --> 00:53:54,212
No.

745
00:53:57,160 --> 00:53:58,128
Carnations?

746
00:53:58,842 --> 00:53:59,874
No.

747
00:54:01,761 --> 00:54:02,829
Flamingo flowers?

748
00:54:05,190 --> 00:54:06,122
Orchids?

749
00:54:07,229 --> 00:54:08,701
Are you going to get it right ever?

750
00:54:11,933 --> 00:54:12,860
What is it then?

751
00:54:14,320 --> 00:54:15,939
I like sunflowers.

752
00:54:19,287 --> 00:54:20,542
They're right in front of you.

753
00:54:24,540 --> 00:54:25,308
Here.

754
00:54:26,178 --> 00:54:28,435
The flower that you like.

755
00:54:31,838 --> 00:54:33,838
There are plenty of beautiful flowers.

756
00:54:34,118 --> 00:54:35,370
Why sunflowers?

757
00:54:38,631 --> 00:54:43,923
Sunflowers refuse to stay in the dark.

758
00:54:45,258 --> 00:54:48,097
They always look for sunlight.

759
00:54:49,876 --> 00:54:53,025
That's probably why I like them.

760
00:55:04,584 --> 00:55:05,932
You're pretty deep.

761
00:55:10,719 --> 00:55:12,377
Do you want it? I'll buy it for you.

762
00:55:18,480 --> 00:55:19,401
It's okay.

763
00:55:20,480 --> 00:55:22,972
Even if you do,

764
00:55:24,805 --> 00:55:26,187
I can't see it.

765
00:55:27,771 --> 00:55:30,163
Let it be with someone with good vision.

766
00:55:31,292 --> 00:55:32,795
It should be happier.

767
00:55:34,427 --> 00:55:35,256
Okay.

768
00:55:37,073 --> 00:55:38,244
This way.

769
00:55:38,430 --> 00:55:39,574
This way, Day.

770
00:55:39,574 --> 00:55:41,455
Can you set it to landscape, Phi?

771
00:55:41,455 --> 00:55:42,275
Sure.

772
00:55:45,177 --> 00:55:45,939
Smile.

773
00:55:46,503 --> 00:55:48,006
One, two, three.

774
00:55:51,939 --> 00:55:53,162
Strike a pose.

775
00:56:00,761 --> 00:56:01,860
Done.

776
00:56:01,860 --> 00:56:02,674
Is it good?

777
00:56:02,836 --> 00:56:03,731
It's good.

778
00:56:11,994 --> 00:56:12,913
Hey.

779
00:56:15,167 --> 00:56:16,701
Can I ask you a favor?

780
00:56:25,651 --> 00:56:26,345
Excuse me.

781
00:56:26,345 --> 00:56:29,453
Did anyone come here and look for that blind man over there?

782
00:56:29,577 --> 00:56:30,588
I have no idea, sir.

783
00:56:30,588 --> 00:56:32,074
Oh, right.

784
00:56:32,074 --> 00:56:32,841
Thank you.

785
00:56:33,214 --> 00:56:34,158
Thank you.

786
00:56:42,312 --> 00:56:43,046
Day.

787
00:56:46,126 --> 00:56:47,081
How was it?

788
00:56:47,205 --> 00:56:48,224
I asked.

789
00:56:50,614 --> 00:56:51,587
No one came.

790
00:56:56,836 --> 00:56:57,646
Forget it.

791
00:57:03,363 --> 00:57:04,648
But I got you something else.

792
00:57:06,605 --> 00:57:07,475
What?

793
00:57:10,886 --> 00:57:11,764
This.

794
00:57:14,808 --> 00:57:16,520
In case somebody could use a drink.

795
00:57:17,780 --> 00:57:19,780
You even know that I don't want to go home yet.

796
00:57:35,301 --> 00:57:36,193
Look.

797
00:57:36,721 --> 00:57:38,606
We practiced dining out so hard

798
00:57:38,787 --> 00:57:40,663
just to end up drinking beer just the two of us.

799
00:57:40,915 --> 00:57:42,138
How sad.

800
00:57:45,466 --> 00:57:47,093
I was stupid

801
00:57:48,340 --> 00:57:50,620
to think he really wanted to see me.

802
00:57:51,940 --> 00:57:53,257
When, actually,

803
00:57:53,882 --> 00:57:55,509
he only said yes out of courtesy.

804
00:57:56,764 --> 00:57:58,174
Why would you think that?

805
00:58:03,024 --> 00:58:06,515
Actually, he didn't want to partner with me.

806
00:58:07,790 --> 00:58:11,032
But the coach matched us.

807
00:58:13,137 --> 00:58:15,013
It's like an arranged marriage.

808
00:58:16,259 --> 00:58:19,812
But what was expected from us wasn't children, but championships.

809
00:58:34,108 --> 00:58:35,456
It's funny how, sometimes,

810
00:58:36,982 --> 00:58:42,585
we put our future in the hands of someone we barely know.

811
00:58:44,498 --> 00:58:46,498
I tried to befriend him,

812
00:58:47,590 --> 00:58:52,696
asked for his name, what he liked, and what he didn't like.

813
00:58:53,916 --> 00:58:56,972
When he's mad, I had to make it up to him.

814
00:58:57,533 --> 00:59:01,583
Because if I didn't, his anger would lead to us losing competitions.

815
00:59:22,081 --> 00:59:26,970
I know I said he should partner with someone else,

816
00:59:30,098 --> 00:59:31,446
but deep down

817
00:59:34,649 --> 00:59:35,904
I'm glad that…

818
00:59:37,585 --> 00:59:39,305
he hasn't found himself a new partner.

819
00:59:50,627 --> 00:59:52,285
If this wasn't about badminton,

820
00:59:53,532 --> 00:59:55,284
I would presume you're talking about your ex.

821
00:59:58,176 --> 00:59:59,073
Phi.

822
01:00:00,409 --> 01:00:04,276
Today when I was in that restaurant,

823
01:00:10,232 --> 01:00:12,046
I felt like a heartbroken man.

824
01:00:20,055 --> 01:00:22,055
I guess I really like him.

825
01:00:38,167 --> 01:00:39,939
It's such a shame.

826
01:00:43,805 --> 01:00:45,246
I should have told him sooner.

827
01:00:46,353 --> 01:00:48,353
When I was still able to see his face.

828
01:01:09,568 --> 01:01:10,322
Day.

829
01:01:13,459 --> 01:01:14,829
Actually, I…

830
01:01:29,514 --> 01:01:30,737
Stunned, aren't you?

831
01:01:31,394 --> 01:01:33,052
To know that I like August.

832
01:01:54,936 --> 01:01:56,128
I finished the beer.

833
01:02:02,235 --> 01:02:03,079
Come on.

834
01:02:03,452 --> 01:02:04,391
Let's go home.

835
01:02:05,201 --> 01:02:06,269
Screw him.

836
01:02:22,734 --> 01:02:23,709
Day.

837
01:02:34,846 --> 01:02:36,101
Honestly,

838
01:02:38,341 --> 01:02:39,939
I'm still not okay.

839
01:03:15,939 --> 01:03:17,939
Directed by Noppharnach Chaiyahwimhon

840
01:03:18,499 --> 01:03:20,344
There is a running race next month.

841
01:03:20,344 --> 01:03:21,438
Would you like to join, young man?

842
01:03:21,477 --> 01:03:23,943
We can't see. How are we supposed to run, Master?

843
01:03:23,943 --> 01:03:26,119
Just pair up with someone with good vision,

844
01:03:26,119 --> 01:03:27,572
so they can guide you the way.

845
01:03:28,459 --> 01:03:29,550
Do you like it?

846
01:03:29,799 --> 01:03:30,708
I do.

847
01:03:34,854 --> 01:03:36,133
Would you like to have dinner with me?

848
01:03:36,133 --> 01:03:37,599
As your what?

849
01:03:37,773 --> 01:03:40,239
What status do you want, Nong Day?

850
01:03:40,239 --> 01:03:41,843
You're such a handsome man.

851
01:03:42,259 --> 01:03:43,389
You realize that?

852
01:03:43,389 --> 01:03:44,734
